# Internationalization Constitution (English-First)

The platform supports multiple languages. English is the primary and default
language and the base bundle for every user-facing string.

## Non-negotiables

- Never hardcode user-facing strings in code. Always reference a message key.
- English base bundle must exist for every key; other locales are additive and
  fall back to English when a key is missing.
- Keys are stable and meaningful; never encode runtime data into keys.
- Locale switching must not change information architecture, layout, or components.

## Backend

- API errors return `error.code`, `error.category`, `error.retryable`, an English
  `error.message`, and `error.messageKey` (`api.error.<category>.<camelCaseCode>`).
- One stable, safe English message per `error.code`; do not vary it per scenario.
- Base bundle: `backend/src/main/resources/i18n/messages_en.properties`.

## Frontend

- Use the i18n catalog with `en` as default and source of truth.
- Add the English key first; components reference keys, never literals.

Detailed workflow: `.cursor/skills/i18n-english-first/SKILL.md`.
